For a newline-free string that the operating system can't use as a file path—for example, one containing an embedded null byte or one that is too long—treat it as calendar data, instead of propagating an :exc:`OSError` from :meth:`Component.from_ical <icalendar.cal.component.Component.from_ical>`. Such input now raises a consistent :exc:`ValueError` across platforms. The string-versus-path boundary is now covered by tests. @uwezkhan
